Defendant Elliot T Oshkeshequoam in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Defendant Elliot T Oshkeshequoam in custody.  Randy Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin with student intern Carlos Pedrava.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE TO EACH OTHER.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS.
Conditions: 
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety;
*  Full time employment/school or a combination of both;
*  No contact with Pick and Save;
*  Participate in the Fatherhood Initiative Program;
*  Obtain a GED;
*  Participate in parenting classes;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
